  <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/hasDescription">
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf>
      <owl:DatatypeProperty rdf:about="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/TextDatatype/hasTextValue">
        <skos:note>Note that although the intended range for this property is Text, we have left the range undefined so that it can be used with tools that do not support rdf:langString.</skos:note>
        <rdfs:label>has text value</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>provides a string value for something, with or without a language tag</skos:definition>
      </owl:DatatypeProperty>
    </rdfs:subPropertyOf>
    <cmns-av:usageNote>This property is a data property, rather than an annotation such as dct:description, enabling it to be used for mapping controlled vocabularies and other literals that are explicit, required attributes of other models.</cmns-av:usageNote>
    <rdfs:label>has description</rdfs:label>
    <skos:note>Note that the hasDescription property defined herein has an implicit range of rdfs:Literal. This is purposeful, so that users can specify any element that has a name with or without a language tag without concern for conflicting datatypes (i.e., xsd:string vs. rdf:langString, which are logically disjoint).</skos:note>
    <skos:definition>provides a textual statement, picture in words, or account that describes something</skos:definition>
  </owl:DatatypeProperty>
  <owl:Class rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Mixin">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#NonSortal"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#SemiRigidType"/>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">A gufo:EndurantType that is both non-sortal and semi-rigid. As a semi-rigid type, it applies necessarily to some of its instances and contingently to some others. As a non-sortal, it captures properties shared by instances of different kinds.

For example, the type "FemaleAnimal" may be considered a gufo:Mixin as it applies necessarily to animals of certain species, e.g., lions and sharks, while it applies contingently to animals of other species such as clownfish and mushroom corals (which may change sex given certain conditions).</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">Mixin</rdfs:label>
  </owl:Class>
