  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://ontology.amt.org/im#leadOfExhibitor">
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Registration"/>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://ontology.amt.org/im#Lead"/>
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf>
      <owl:FunctionalProperty rdf:about="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#inheresIn">
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">inheresIn</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Identifies the gufo:ConcreteIndividual in which the gufo:Aspect inheres. Inherence is a sort of existential dependence. The identified concrete individual is the "bearer" of the aspect.

For example, the color of an object inheres in the object and the average speed of a flight inheres in the flight.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#Aspect"/>
        <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://purl.org/nemo/gufo#ConcreteIndividual"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty"/>
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty"/>
      </owl:FunctionalProperty>
    </rdfs:subPropertyOf>
    <rdfs:comment>Links a Lead (booth-scan event) to the Registration that operated the booth -- usually an im:ExhibitorRecord, occasionally an im:AmtFacility for badges scanned at AMT-operated venue spaces (member lounges, international lounge). Range widened from im:ExhibitorRecord to im:Registration so AmtFacility scans participate in the same exact-1 invariant.</rdfs:comment>
    <rdfs:label>lead of exhibitor</rdfs:label>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
