  <owl:Class rdf:about="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/Name">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/Designation"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf>
      <owl:Restriction rdf:nodeID="N0c1b5dadb9104869a508ffe237d9af9f">
        <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
        <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://www.omg.org/spec/Commons/Designators/isNameOf"/>
      </owl:Restriction>
    </rdfs:subClassOf>
    <skos:note>In ISO 1087, a name may be an appellation and is defined as a term that is applied to a group of objects whose relevant properties are identical, whereas a proper name is a designation that represents an individual object.</skos:note>
    <cmns-av:adaptedFrom>ISO/IEC 11179-3 Information technology - Metadata registries (MDR) - Registry metamodel and basic attributes, Third edition, 2013-02-15, clause 3.2.83</cmns-av:adaptedFrom>
    <rdfs:label>name</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition>designation for something by a linguistic expression</skos:definition>
    <cmns-av:explanatoryNote>Note that unlike symbols and other designations, a name is explicitly not linguistically neutral.</cmns-av:explanatoryNote>
  </owl:Class>
